- 'shining star' refers to the model with the highest average GMean value;
- 'most dedicated gardener' refers to the user with the most frequent access logs to the top models;
- 'visits to the top models' refers to access logs for the models with the highest average GMean values.

- 'data scientist' refers to users with the role of data scientist in the `users` table;
- 'F1 score macro' is a performance metric that measures the model's ability to predict classes, with a higher score indicating better performance;
- 'average F1 score macro' is the mean F1 score across all evaluations for a given model.

- 'Blossoms of Neural Network' refers to models of type 'Neural Network';
- 'Fully pollinated by completed evaluations' refers to evaluations that have a status of 'completed';
- 'Visited by the evaluators' refers to the total number of evaluations conducted;
- 'Average exceeds a single visit' refers to the condition that the average number of evaluations must be greater than 1.

- "stands tallest" refers to the model with the highest average accuracy;
- "garden of accuracy" is a metaphor for the dataset where models are evaluated based on their performance;
- "reaching the pinnacle of performance" means achieving the highest average accuracy.

- "average accuracy" is a measure of how well a model performs on average across multiple evaluations;
- "macro F1 score" is a metric that considers the harmonic mean of precision and recall for all classes, giving equal weight to each class;
- "model details" include the name, type, creator's username, version, description, algorithm, and hyperparameters.

- "High average accuracy" refers to an average accuracy greater than 90%;
- "Significant total evaluation time" refers to a total evaluation time greater than 10 seconds;
- "Good average GMean value" refers to an average GMean value greater than 60%.

- "Blossoms" metaphorically refers to machine learning models;
- "Frequently evaluated" means the models have a high number of evaluations;
- "Average learning instances" refers to the mean number of data points used for training;
- "Average evaluation time" is the mean time taken for each evaluation;
- "Classification correctness" is the percentage of correct predictions;
- "Macro F1 score" is a measure of the model's performance that considers both precision and recall.

- GMean value is a measure of the geometric mean of the recall values for all classes, which is useful in imbalanced datasets;
- The model with the highest GMean value is typically considered the best performer because it balances the performance across all classes;
- The GMean value ranges from 0 to 1, with 1 being the best possible score.

- "Recall for class 0" is a performance metric that measures the proportion of actual positive cases that were correctly identified by the model;
- "Average accuracy" is the mean accuracy across multiple evaluations of the model;
- "Evaluations" refer to the different instances where the model's performance was measured.

